rls to join in 2019 and embracing progressive ideologies. \n\nDespite the drastic reduction in numbers and the rebranding from \"Boy Scouts of America\" to \"Scouting America\" in early 2025, local troops continue to operate. However, many observers argue that the organization has lost its distinctive identity and cultural relevance, with attendance at major events like the National Jamboree plummeting from over 70,000 in the 1970s to just 15,000 in 2023.  While the entity exists and continues to function locally, its national influence and membership base have shrunk to a fraction of their former size. \n\nAI-generated answer. Please verify critical facts.", "author": "SenorTrumper", "created": 1778993329971, "profile_picture": "jau0FhbIn31Y", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Captntrouble", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "RIP Boy Scouts of America", "last_comment_created": 1778995283753, "content": "<p>Asking ChatGTP</p>\n<p>Is the Boy Scouts organization dying?</p>\n<p>Yes, the Boy Scouts of America is in a state of severe decline and is widely described by critics and analysts as &quot;dying&quot; or in &quot;free fall,&quot; although the organization itself remains operational and has recently rebranded to Scouting America.</p>\n<p>The organization has faced a catastrophic drop in membership, losing approximately 62% of its members between 2019 and 2021, with total membership falling from over 4 million in the 1970s to roughly 1 million today.  This decline is attributed to a combination of factors, including the $2.5 billion sexual abuse settlement that forced the organization into Chapter 11 bankruptcy, social shifts away from traditional youth groups, and criticism that the organization abandoned its core mission of developing young men by allowing girls to join in 2019 and embracing progressive ideologies.</p>\n<p>Despite the drastic reduction in numbers and the rebranding from &quot;Boy Scouts of America&quot; to &quot;Scouting America&quot; in early 2025, local troops continue to operate. However, many observers argue that the organization has lost its distinctive identity and cultural relevance, with attendance at major events like the National Jamboree plummeting from over 70,000 in the 1970s to just 15,000 in 2023.  While the entity exists and continues to function locally, its national influence and membership base have shrunk to a fraction of their former size.</p>\n<p>AI-generated answer. Please verify critical facts.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 20, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "\ud83e\udd21\ud83c\udf0e\u00a0\u00a0HONK\u00a0\u00a0HONK\u00a0\u00a0\ud83c\udf0e\ud83e\udd21", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2055711916174287333", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsURWOMF", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 39, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8622623, "raw_content": "", "author": "KuzoKevin", "created": 1778980146833, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "greatpumpkin", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsURWOMF.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/theQbanguy/status/2055711916174287333", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Owie...", "las